          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p class="pb-6 pl-12 text-slate-500 text-sm leading-relaxed max-w-xl">
              A deposit bond is an insurance policy that acts as a substitute for the cash deposit. It guarantees the vendor that the 10% deposit will be paid at settlement.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item border-b border-stone-300 reveal delay-100 cursor-pointer group" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
